Package bauernhof.preset

General classes, enums and interfaces of the preset.
You should probably start by looking at the following classes in here:
  • Settings, ArgumentParser and OptionalFeature
  • Logger
  • GameConfiguration and GameConfigurationParser
  • Player, PlayerGUIAccess and ImmutableList
Don't forget to also look at the other packages:
  • bauernhof.preset.card
  • bauernhof.preset.networking
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GameConfiguration
    A game configuration.
    GameConfigurationParser
    A parser for a GameConfiguration.
    Player
    The API for interacting with the player.
    PlayerGUIAccess
    An instance of PlayerGUIAccess is allowed to be given to the HUMAN Player via its constructor.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArgumentParser
    Parse arguments from the command line and store them as settings.
    Either<L,​R>
    A data type that can only contain either the left or the right value but not both nor neither.
    ImmutableList<E>
    An immutable view on a list.
    Logger
    A simple logger for creating fancy log outputs.
    Move
    A move made by a player during a round.
    PresetInfo
    Information about the current build of the preset.
    Settings
    The settings for the program.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    LogLevel
    The different possible loglevels for the Logger.
    OptionalFeature
    Optional features you may want to implement.
    PlayerType
    The different personalities of players.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    GameConfigurationException
    An exception that may be thrown while parsing a game configuration indicating that the game configuration is invalid.
